Installation
************

   Chaos is developed using Kickstart 3.0 and should run on any Amiga using
Kickstart 2.0 or higher. Chaos uses the @{b}locale.library@{ub}, but supports other
languages without it! Bad luck for people still using Kickstart 1.3 or
lower -- and another reason to upgrade. (Believe me: 2.x is a wonderful
thing for programmers and users too.)

   What Chaos needs is the @{b}mui.library@{ub}, version 2.0 or newer. MUI (@{b}Magic
user interface@{ub}) is shareware and hence freely distributable; you find it
for example on Aminet (Directory @{b}/pub/aminet/dev/gui@{ub}) or on the Fish CDs. I
admit, that using a shareware program as part of a really free program is a
bit of contradiction. But the advantages of using MUI seemed overwhelming
to me, MUI is cheap (15$ for the registration) and after all: In principle
it's possible, to use MUI without being registered. However, I strongly
encourage any Chaos user to become registered.

   A hard-drive is not required, but very useful (as always) and installing
Chaos @{i}and@{ui} MUI on one floppy disk could make problems. (I did not try it.)

   Installation is rather simple: Just unpack the file @{b}Chaos.lha@{ub}.  (I
suppose, you have done right now. :-) If not, use the following command:

   @{i}lha x Chaos5.4bin.lha@{ui}

(You will find LhA on the fish-disks for example.) If you want, you can
unpack the sources (in @{b}Chaos5.4src.lha@{ub}) as well.

   The installation is finished now! But possibly you don't like to have a
special Chaos-directory? To perform the installation you can use the
Install-Skript in that case by simply double-clicking the Install icon.
When running it in Novice-Mode it simply copies the program to @{b}c:@{ub}, the
default-icon to @{b}s:@{ub} and the Catalogs you wish to @{b}Locale:Catalogs@{ub}. The skript
needs the program @{b}Installer@{ub} which is part of the OS since Workbench 2.1.
There is a freely distributable version of this program which you should
find on the Fish-disks too or on Aminet (directory @{b}/pub/aminet/util/misc@{ub}).

   What the installer script does: When using @{b}locale.library@{ub}, Chaos needs
to find the Directory @{b}Catalogs@{ub}. This should be a subdirectory of the
directory from which the program is started or might be copied to @{b}locale:@{ub}
using the command

   @{i}copy Catalogs locale:Catalogs all@{ui}

Without @{b}locale.library@{ub} you have to use the built in english language.
Currently there is only a german catalogfile. The file @{b}src/NewCatalog.ct@{ub}
can be used to create new catalogfiles.  (Please send them to me. I will
include them in new versions of the program.) Note, that Chaos is able to
use catalogs on Workbench 2.0! Possibly you have to create a directory
@{b}Locale:catalogs@{ub} in that case.

   Another subdirectory should be called @{b}s@{ub} containing the file
@{b}Chaos_project.info@{ub}, which is the project-icon, that tournaments will
receive when being saved by Chaos, and the file @{b}Chaos_Menu@{ub} which is
required for the @{b}Special@{ub} menu. It might be changed for example using
@{b}IconEd@{ub}. Another place to install this could be @{b}s:@{ub}. In that case execute

   @{i}copy s s: all@{ui}

and remove the subdirectory @{b}s@{ub}.

   There is a subdirectory @{b}Rexx@{ub} containing some example scripts. These show
how to use Chaos from an ARexx program. Probably you wish to copy these as
well.

   It should be noted that Chaos uses some special characters which are not
included in all fonts. Please ensure that your Workbench uses fonts which
contain all 256 Amiga-characters!

   The program is started from either CLI or workbench. One thing is
important: Chaos uses algorithms working in a recursive way and needs very
much stack therefore! Suggested are 50 Bytes per player and 4000 bytes for
the system.  A stack of 20000 bytes should be sufficient and is set as
default in the Chaos-Icon. The stacksize is changed using the Info-menuitem
in the workbench screen or using the CLI-command @{b}stack@{ub} depending on how you
start Chaos. The latter should be done by inserting the following line in
@{b}s:Shell-Startup@{ub} or executing the line manually everytime before starting
Chaos:

   @{i}stack 20000@{ui}


