The ARexx-Port: Chaos as a batch program
****************************************

   Using the port name @{b}CHAOS.1@{ub} you can control Chaos from other programs
via ARexx. Even more: You don't need the GUI of Chaos, that's why you have
the @{b}NOWINDOW@{ub} option.


 @{" Commands " Link "Commands"}         Possible ARexx commands
 @{" Own Menuitems " Link "Own Menuitems"}    Inserting ARexx commands into an own menu


@EndNode

@Node "Commands" "Chaos_english.guide/Commands"
@Next "Own Menuitems"
@Toc "ARexx"

Possible ARexx commands
=======================

   The ARexx commands correspond to menu items, you should therefore
understand them immediately. Of course you cannot use an ARexx command,
when the corresponding menu item is disabled. For example it is not
possible to sort the table due to Buchholz points in a round robin
tournament or make new pairings while the user enters results.

   This are the commands:

 - : NewTournament @{i}NAME/A,@{ui}  @{i}FORCE/S@{ui}
     Creates a new tournament with the given name. You are asked for
     confirmation, if the current tournament isn't saved. This can be
     suppressed using the FORCE option. See @{"Project-New" Link "Project"}.

 - : LoadTournament @{i}FILE/A,@{ui}  @{i}FORCE/S@{ui}
     Loads the given tournament. FORCE works like above. See @{"Project-Load" Link "Project"}.

 - : SaveTournament @{i}FILE/A,@{ui}  @{i}ICON/S@{ui}
     Saves the current tournament in the given file. You can create an icon
     using the ICON option. See @{"Project-Save" Link "Project"}.

 - : AddPlayer @{i}NAME/A,@{ui}  @{i}STREET/K,@{ui}  @{i}VILLAGE/K,@{ui}  @{i}CHESSCLUB/K,@{ui}  @{i}BIRTHDAY/K,@{ui}
          @{i}PHONE/K,@{ui}  @{i}RATING/K,@{ui}  @{i}ELO/K,@{ui}  @{i}FLAGS/K,@{ui}  @{i}NOUSER/S@{ui}
     Enters a new player. A name must be present. Flags are a string
     containing one or more of the characters s (Senior), j (Junior), w
     (Woman) and a-e (Junior A, ...,  Junior E). RATING is the DWZ or
     another national rating. See @{"Player-input" Link "Player-input"}. See @{"Players-Add" Link "Players"}.  The
     option NOUSER suppresses error requesters.

 - : ModifyPlayer @{i}PLAYER/A,@{ui}  @{i}NAME/K,@{ui}  @{i}STREET/K,@{ui}  @{i}VILLAGE/K,@{ui}  @{i}CHESSCLUB/K,@{ui}
          @{i}BIRTHDAY/K,@{ui}  @{i}PHONE/K,@{ui}  @{i}RATING/K,@{ui}  @{i}ELO/K,@{ui}  @{i}FLAGS/K@{ui}
     Modifies the data of the player whose name is PLAYER. Only the given
     fields are modified, for example

     @{b}ModifyPlayer "Widmann, Jochen" NAME "Wiedmann, Jochen"@{ub}

     modifies the name only. See @{"Players-Modify" Link "Players"}.  NOUSER suppresses error
     requesters.

 - : DeletePlayer @{i}PLAYER/A,@{ui}  @{i}FORCE/S@{ui}
     deletes the given player (or marks him as withdrawn in a Swiss pairing
     tournament). You are asked for confirmation without the FORCE option.
     See @{"Players-Delete" Link "Players"}.

 - : SetPlayer @{i}PLAYER/A,@{ui}  @{i}INIT/S,@{ui}  @{i}FORCE/S@{ui}
     Sets the given player for the next pairings. For example if you want to
     force the pairings of players 3-5 and 2-4 and give player 17 an one
     point bye you execute the SetPlayer command for players 3, 5, 2, 4 and
     17 in that order and call DoPairings after that. You see: It works
     like the interactive setting of games. See @{"Setting games" Link "Setting games"}.

     You can remove the games that have been set so far using the INIT
     option.  This must be called @{i}before@{ui} executing DoPairings of course.)
     You might enter a new player together with the INIT option.

     Chaos declines pairing the same players a second time or giving a one
     point bye to a player who already had one. You are asked for
     confirmation, if players should be paired, who had one and the same
     color in the last two rounds. (This can be suppressed with the FORCE
     option.) Normally Chaos determines, who will receive the white pieces.
     However, this can be changed using the SETCOLOR option. It @{i}must@{ui} be
     given when setting the second player who will receive the black
     pieces. It is ignored when setting the first player. See
     @{"Round-Pairings" Link "Round"}.

 - : DoPairings @{i}SWISSPAIRING/S,@{ui}  @{i}ROUNDROBIN/S,@{ui}  @{i}ROUNDROBINSHIFT/S,@{ui}
          @{i}NOUSER/S@{ui}
     This command creates new pairings. You must give one of the options
     SWISSPAIRING, ROUNDROBIN (FIDE system) or ROUNDROBINSHIFT (shift
     system) before creating the first round. The setting games window will
     be opened without the NOUSER option and allows the user to enter new
     games.

     Chaos declines to draw new games, if you gave a player an one point
     bye, but the number of active players is even, See @{"Pairings" Link "Round"}.

 - : EnterResult @{i}WHITE/A,@{ui}  @{i}BLACK/A,@{ui}  @{i}RESULT/A/N,@{ui}  @{i}NOTPLAYED/S@{ui}
     The result (2 = white wins, 1 = draw, 0 = black wins, -1 = result
     missing) of the match between players WHITE and BLACK is entered using
     this command.  The NOTPLAYED option should be used, if the match
     didn't took place.  See @{"Round-Enter results" Link "Round"}.

   The following output commands need a filename. The given file will
receive the output in Ascii format. You can use the names @{b}prt:@{ub} for output
to the printer in draft mode or @{b}prt:LQ@{ub} for letter quality.

 - : PlayerList @{i}FILE/A,@{ui}  @{i}SHORT/S@{ui}
     Prints the list of players. The long format is used without the SHORT
     option. See @{"List of players" Link "Output"}.

 - : InternalRatings @{i}FILE/A@{ui}
     Prints the internal ratings. See @{"Internal ratings" Link "Output"}.

 - : Table @{i}FILE/A,@{ui}  @{i}TABMODE/K/N,@{ui}  @{i}PLRMODE/K/N@{ui}
     Prints the current table. The table is sorted due to the TABMODE (0 =
     simple, 1 = Buchholz, 2 = extended Buchholz, 3 = Sonneborn-Berger) and
     PLRMODE determines, which players should be included into the table (0
     = all, 1 = seniors, 2 = juniors, 3 = women, 4, ..., 8 = Juniors A, ...,
     Juniors E). Defaults are simpe and all. See @{"Table" Link "Output"}.

 - : Round @{i}FILE/A,@{ui}  @{i}NUMBER/N@{ui}
     Prints the given round; default is the last round. See @{"Round" Link "Output"}.

 - : TableOfProgress @{i}FILE/A,@{ui}  @{i}TABMODE/K/N@{ui}
     Prints the table of progress. See the table command for TABMODE.  See
     @{"Table of progress" Link "Output"}.

 - : CrossTable @{i}FILE/A,@{ui}  @{i}TEX/S@{ui}
     Prints the crosstable. TeX source is created with the TEX option. It is
     possible, to use this option together with the filename @{b}prt:@{ub}, but this
     doesn't call TeX and prints the source on the printer instead, that's
     why this probably doesn't make much sense. See @{"Cross table" Link "Output"}.

 - : PlayerCards @{i}FILE/A,@{ui}  @{i}TEX/S@{ui}
     Prints the player cards. See the CrossTable command for the TEX option.
     See @{"Player cards" Link "Output"}.

 - : DWZReport @{i}FILE/A@{ui}
     Prints the DWZ report. It isn't possible, to suppress the requester
     asking for a players birthday, if this is missing. See @{"DWZ-ratings" Link "DWZ-ratings"}.

 - : Window @{i}ON/S,@{ui}  @{i}OFF/S@{ui}
     Switches the main window on or off. See @{"Startup" Link "Startup"}.


@EndNode

