Inserting ARexx commands into an own menu
=========================================

   Once you have created an own ARexx script you probably wish to execute
this from Chaos itself. This is possible by creating an own menu calling
this script.

   Chaos is looking for a file called @{b}s/Chaos_Menu@{ub} at startup. (This name
can be changed by using the option @{b}MENUFILE@{ub}. See @{"Startup" Link "Startup"}.) If this isn't
found, Chaos is looking for @{b}s:Chaos_Menu@{ub} as well.

   A menu called @{b}Special@{ub} will be created, if one of this files is found.
The file defines some menuitems, which will be inserted into the menu.
Each menuitem is represented by two subsequent lines in the file: One for
the label and one for a shell command which will be executed, if the
corresponding menuitem is selected. (See @{b}s/Chaos_Menu@{ub} for an example.)

   Notes:
  1. Chaos is not ready to receive commands until the Shell command
     terminates.  Especially Chaos cannot execute ARexx commands while your
     Shell command is running! Hence you probably need to use the command
     @{b}Run@{ub}.

  2. Intuition cannot maintain more than 31 menuitems.

   Two scripts are available yet. These should supply you with examples, but
possibly might be useful for themselves. Both contain a description of how
to use them


 @{" PrintTable " Link "PrintTable"}       Formatting own tables
 @{" UpdateRatings " Link "UpdateRatings"}    Exporting the new computed ratings into a database


@EndNode

@Node "PrintTable" "Chaos_english.guide/PrintTable"
@Next "UpdateRatings"
@Toc "Own Menuitems"

PrintTable: Formatting own tables
---------------------------------

   A swiss user group wanted a special formatted table: The points should be
behind the players and the chessclub should appear as well. This script
realizes it. It makes Chaos to write the current table and the list of
players into special files. This are read by the script and the modified
table gets printed.

   There should be no problem to understand the script, except for one
point: All this data dosn't fit on one line in any case! (Player and
chessclub names may be up to 30 characters long.) The script solves this by
cutting these names eventually.


@EndNode

@Node "UpdateRatings" "Chaos_english.guide/UpdateRatings"
@Prev "PrintTable"
@Toc "Own Menuitems"

UpdateRatings: Exporting new computed ratings into a database
-------------------------------------------------------------

   The menuitem @{b}Import@{ub} makes it possible to have a player database, as
already mentioned. (see @{"Players" Link "Players"}) This script makes it possible, to update
the ratings of the database. You have to supply the script with a database
name, either by calling it with @{b}UpdateRatings.rexx databasename@{ub} (The name
must be inserted in @{b}s/Chaos_Menu@{ub} in that case.) or by selecting the
database with the asl requester, if the script is called without a database
name. (This assumes the existence of @{b}c:RequestFile@{ub}.)

   The script stores the current tournament in @{b}t:CurrentTournament@{ub}, makes
Chaos to write the new ratings into a file and load the database. The ARexx
command @{b}ModifyPlr@{ub} is used to update the ratings in the database which is
saved again finally and the current tournament is restored.


